The forces of the mega strike gather together
The unions of the League and the National Association of Workers' Councils will constitute, on Friday, their strike commission which will be responsible for coordinating the indeterminate strike of Monday.
On Saturday, a general protest meeting will be held and on Monday, the day of the final vote on the Health Fund Act, the strike will begin.
This action will certainly cause major traffic stops because rail traffic will be almost completely stopped and BKV's employees (common transport company) will also strike until 1 p.m.
The Unions of the League will announce, Friday afternoon, the details of their Monday strike, organized with the National Association of Workers' Councils.
The LIGA - MOSZ strike commission will also be set up and will serve as a coordinator of the actions on Monday.
On Saturday, a general protest assembly will be held and, as of Monday, the organizations joining the strike will stop work for an indefinite period if they fail to reach agreement with the government.
This means that the date of the end of the strike, starting from the day of the vote in parliament on the health funds law, is not defined.
If the National Assembly does not pass the Health Fund Act, the unions will immediately withdraw the strike appeal.
On the other hand, if the law is passed, the strike committees will meet and decide on the next steps to be taken.
According to the Monday agenda of the National Assembly, it is likely that the vote on the Health Fund Act will take place only late at night or at night.
Due to the planned strike on Monday, important stops are planned in traffic: the railways will stop work for an indefinite period and during the morning part of the public transport in Budapest and more than half of the companies Volán are likely to be stopped.
At the same time, at different points in the country, half of the road will be blocked as well.
Many unions and civil organizations have joined the strike call, and the list of them is constantly updated on the League site.
Some organizations report an indeterminate strike, others reported a temporary stoppage.
Until Thursday afternoon the MÁV (Hungarian Railways) and the Free Railway Union (VDSZSZ) have failed to reach agreement on minimum services, or, as Christmas parties approach, more and more people take the train.
According to current communications, public transport in Budapest will strike from the beginning of service until 1 p.m., Budapest Airport between 7 a.m. and 9 a.m., the Industrial Syndicats of Electricity and Thermal Energy of the League will strike for 4 a.m., the Teachers' Union and the Democratic Teachers Union have called for a strike for 2 a.m. and 2 a.m. to 8 a.m. respectively.
The National Association of Physicians will strike across the country alternately, the Health and Social Sector Employees' Union (EDDSZ) attached to the SEFS will hold a two-hour warning strike.
The most important of the four claims, formulated by the League, requires the government to withdraw its proposal on health reform and submit a new approach to social debate.
The second claim requires that the new method of calculating retirement to be put in place from next year be introduced in several stages.
The third claim requires a guarantee, in terms of retirement before the legal age, that would allow the system to pass on the functions that deserve it before 2010.
The fourth reason for the action is the rejection by the Free Railway Union (VDSZSZ), attached to the League Unions, the proposal of the Ministry of Economy and Transport concerning secondary railway lines and the expectation of another proposal.
Political Capital: The Hungarian Guard has increased the risk country
According to the Risk Analysis Division of Political Capital (Risk Analysing Division), the Hungarian Guard's activity, formed last August, with the support of the Jobbik Magyarszágért Mozgalom (Mouvement pour une miglior Hungary) increases, in several respects, the political risk of Hungary and the region.
In its "risk warning", the society points out that, in relation to the activity of the Hungarian Guard, the greatest political risk is already that "in the short term aggressive ethnic clashes can occur following the worsening ethnic tension already existing between the Gypsies and non-Typsy people of Hungary".
The Research Institute added that the Hungarian Guard's policy strategy likely to lead to this situation is the main reason.
As they say, this is due to one of the main shortcomings of Hungarian political actors: "the public actors have passed the public debate on the Roma case to representatives of the radical and extreme political groupings that have based a political strategy on the dispute between the Gypsies and the Hungarians".
The problem is exacerbated, normal dialogue becomes impossible, extremists are strengthened and aggressive conflicts are more likely, they say.
However, according to the research institute, the Hungarian and international media's activity "has significantly deteriorated Hungary's image abroad, particularly with regard to confidence in the stability and democratic maturity of the country".
They recall that, following greater publicity given to the reorganization of Hungarian radical and extreme right-wing groups since the fall of 2006, many associations have been established in Hungary since the summer of 2007 giving the name "national self-defense association".
"The common feature of these gatherings is that they define themselves as a civil organization while publicly declaring the preparation of their adherents for defence missions (catastrophes, national defence, law enforcement), armies if necessary, in addition, referring to the incapacity of the police, the army, in other words the state," they added.
They pointed out that everything was based on the method that, based on the grudge of the society of politics and parties, seeks to disguise different political ambitions in a civil aspect.
The emphasis on the civil character and status of association therefore only serves to avoid the legal pitfalls of the registration of these associations in the court but they are also a political strategy.
The analysis indicates that the Hungarian Guard activity is a factor that also increases the risk in relation to neighbourhood relations.
