The Federal Reserve Bank, the European Central Bank and the English, Swiss and Canadian central banks have decided to combat the financial market crisis together.
More than $100 billion will thus be placed on monetary markets through auctions.
It will be for banks to sell, through an auction system, interest rates to which they are ready to borrow money.
